pageContext.claim: “So we're going to be at 115,000. That 115,000 could be two-and-a-half or 3 million lives. And it's all too many. One is too many. As you know, one is too many. It should have never happened.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is grievously wrong in claiming that coronavirus deaths would stop at 115,000. The disease was still spreading, as his own public health advisers were stressing, and therefore the death toll was continuing to climb.
